{"title_page": "James Patterson bibliography", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia bibliography}}\n:''See [[James Patterson]] for information about this author.''\n\nThis '''James Patterson bibliography''' contains the list of books written by [[James Patterson]]. He has written or co-written many \"Bookshots\" or novellas, and has co-written books with many authors. The list below separates the works into four main categories: fiction written for adults, for young adults and for children, and non-fiction.<ref>{{cite web |title=a-z |url=http://www.jamespatterson.com/books.php#a-z |work=James Patterson: The official web site}}</ref>\n\n== Fiction written for adults ==\n\n=== Novels ===\n\n;''Cross'' series:\n* [[Alex Cross (novel series)|''Alex Cross'' series]]:\n*# ''[[Along Came a Spider (novel)|Along Came a Spider]]'' (1993), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69364-6}}\n*# ''[[Kiss the Girls (novel)|Kiss the Girls]]'' (1995), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69370-7}}\n*# ''[[Jack & Jill (novel)|Jack and Jill]]'' (1996), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69371-4}}\n*# ''[[Cat and Mouse (novel)|Cat and Mouse]]'' (1997), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69329-5}}\n*# ''[[Pop Goes the Weasel (novel)|Pop Goes the Weasel]]'' (1999), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69328-8}}\n*# ''[[Roses Are Red (novel)|Roses Are Red]]'' (2000), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69325-7}}\n*# ''[[Violets Are Blue (novel)|Violets Are Blue]]'' (2001), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69323-3}}\n*# ''[[Four Blind Mice]]'' (2002), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-69300-4}}\n*# ''[[The Big Bad Wolf (novel)|The Big Bad Wolf]]'' (2003), Boston: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-60290-7}}\n*# ''[[London Bridges]]'' (2004), New York: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-71059-6}}\n*# ''[[Mary, Mary (novel)|Mary, Mary]]'' (2005), New 