 Lennon'' (expected publication: 2020)\n\n;History:\n* ''The Murder of King Tut'' (2009), with [[Martin Dugard (author)|Martin Dugard]], New York: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-03404-3}}<ref>{{cite book|last=Patterson |first=James |last2=Dugard |first2=Martin |date=2009 |title=The Murder of King Tut |location=New York |publisher=Little, Brown and Company |isbn=978-0-316-03404-3 |url=https://archive.org/details/murderofkingtut00patt }}</ref>\n\n;Politics:\n* ''Trump vs. Clinton: In Their Own Words'' (2016), Bookshots {{ISBN|9780316546508}}\n\n;Sociology:\n* ''The Day America Told the Truth'' (1991), with Peter Kim, New York: Prentice Hall Press {{ISBN|9780134634807}}<ref>{{cite book|last=Patterson |first=James |last2=Kim |first2=Peter |date=1991 |title=The Day America Told the Truth |location=New York |publisher=Prentice Hall Press |isbn=9780134634807 |url=https://archive.org/details/dayamericatold00patt }}</ref>\n* ''The Second American Revolution: The People's Plan for Fixing America-Before Its Too Late'' (1994), with Peter Kim, New York: William Morrow and Company {{ISBN|9780688117306}}\n\n;True events:\n* ''Filthy Rich'' (2016), with [[John Connolly (author)|John Connolly]] and Tim Malloy, New York: Little, Brown and Company {{ISBN|978-0-316-27405-0}}\n* ''All-American Murder: The Rise and Fall of Aaron Hernandez, the Superstar Whose Life Ended on Murderers' Row'' (2018), with Alex Abramovich and Mike Harvkey\n* ''Discovery's Murder is Forever'' series:\n** ''Murder, Interrupted'' (2018), Grand Central Publishing {{ISBN|978-1-538-74472-7}}\n** ''Home Sweet Murder'' (2018), Grand Central Publishing {{ISBN|978-1-538-74481-9}}\n** ''Murder Beyond The Grave'' (2018), Grand Central Publishing {{ISBN|978-1-538-74482-6}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{James Patterson}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Patterson, James}}\n[[Category:Novels by James Patterson| ]]\n[[Category:Bibliographies by writer]]\n[[Category:Bibliographies of American writers]]\n", "name_user": "Da